First, because the loan has an application charge of $4,300, we add the loan application fee to the loan amount to establish the loan's present value. As a result, we'll utilize the formula:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Present value} &=\text{Loan application fee}+\text{Loan amount}

\end{aligned}$$

Since the periodic payment to be calculated is monthly, divide the interest rate of 5.1% over 12 to determine the monthly rate we will consider.

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Rate} &=\dfrac{0.051}{12}
\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{0.425\%}
\end{aligned}$$

Therefore the monthly rate is 0.425%.
